,Neither of those (the inner-loop lock and unlock) need be there in the code as posted. the `.wait(...)` unlatches the mutex going into the wait, and the mutex is reacquired upon exiting the wait. If there is work to be done concurrently you can unlock the `lk` once it is acquired, and relock `lk` before swinging around to the next while-iteration. Once you hand off `nodelistaccessmutex` to `lk`, you shouldn't touch it directly again. And I also question whether that nodeStack should be a value-param.
